<exploration xml:id="warm-preguntasNosotros-cuantosEstamos" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"> 

<title>Preguntas sobre nosotros: ¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</title>

<statement>
  <p>¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</p>
</statement>

<solution>
  <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
  <p>Sample response:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>We can count all of the students.</li>
  </ul>
</solution>


<!-- ============================================================== 
   Notas profesor <prelude> (se pueden mostrar previo al enunciado)                      
===================================================================  -->
<prelude component="profesor"> 

  <!-- Estándares CCSS asociados -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="ccss-actividad-titulo"/></title> 
    <ul>
      <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-addressing"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-K-CC-A-1" text="custom">K.CC.A.1</xref>
      </li>
      <li>
        <custom ref="ccss-buildingTowards"/>
        <xref ref="ccss-K-CC-B-4-a" text="custom">K.CC.B.4.a</xref>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Tiempo recomendado -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="recommended-time-titulo"/></title>
    <p>10 minutos</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Introducción de la actividad -->  
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>The purpose of this warm-up is for students to experience part of the Questions About Us routine. Students continue to engage in this routine throughout the section, focused on answering <q>¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</q>. In this activity students associate one number with one person as they count the students in the class. As students share answers to questions such as <q>¿Cómo podemos averiguar cuántos estamos hoy aquí?</q> and <q>¿Conté correctamente los estudiantes?</q> they are beginning to explain their reasoning and construct viable arguments (MP3).</p>
    <p>While the teacher counts the students in the class, students count along to practice the verbal count sequence.</p>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Materiales requeridos de la actividad -->
  <!-- <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="materials-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[@@@@@@@@@]</p>
  </paragraphs> -->

  <!-- Launch -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="launch-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li><q>¿Cómo podemos averiguar cuántos estamos aquí?</q></li>
      <li>30 seconds: quiet think time</li>
      <li>Share responses.</li>
      <li>Monitor for students who suggest touching and counting each student.</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

  <!-- Instrucciones para el desarrollo de la actividad -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="instructions-teacher-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++++]</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Count the students, saying one number for each student.</li>
      <li>“¿Cuántos estamos hoy aquí?” // “How many of us are here today?”</li>
    </ul>
  </paragraphs>

</prelude>


